defaultidefaultidefault. A summary of our perspectivedefault&#xa0;default&#xa0;default“A wider perspectivedefault.default”default&#xa0;
defaultThe abuse of 
defaulteven one 
defaultChildren’
defaults Home
default resident is shocking.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe need to set aside whether we are 
defaultfrom government, private sector or charity and work together to stringently understand how we can bring about improvements in the way we care for looked after children so as to do everything we can to avoid such instances.
default&#xa0;
defaultThose with insight into the way 
defaultthat the systems work within local authority and children’s homes, but who have not seen details of investigations into the cases in Rochdale and elsewhere can only think about how we ourselves have operated and how we might have prevented the abuse. We ca
defaultn only therefore begin to offer the inquiry the questions it may need to ask of the Department for Education to ensure that the most experienced minds have been applied to analyzing the fine detail of 
defaulthow the cases came about.
default&#xa0;
defaultThere would appear to be som
defaulte worthwhile regulation and systems enhancements being proposed that specifically target some areas where weaknesses may be present. 
default&#xa0;
defaultIt is our view however that a wider perspective is needed. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe current marketplace of children’s homes services has evo
defaultlved without strategic vision related to need at a national, regional, or even sometimes at a local level. 
default&#xa0;
defaultThe relationships of purchasers and providers do not 
defaultcurrently 
defaultcreate an environment that attracts investment or innovation, and instead has co
defaultnsid
defaulterable financial pressures that add to tensions between parties who should be working together. 
defaultThe risk is therefore that such pressures (or just the perception that there may be such pressures) may impinge upon the paramount need to act promptly in the b
defaultest interests of the children placed.
default This is the case on both the part of the provider and of the purchaser.
default&#xa0;
defaultWe need a children’s homes system where the very staff in daily contact with the young person are empowered to keep that young person safe, come what may. 
default&#xa0;
defaultWe need a system where the adults involved are skilled and professional enough to remove the pressu
defaultres of financial constraints and private vs. public sector tensions, so that the child receives a focused, responsive and excellent service at all times.
default&#xa0;
defaultIt’s about people not 
defaultjust about 
defaultprocess.
